 	-There are lots of types in std_msg pckg like:
 bool, byte, char, intxxx, floatxxx, empty, uintxxx, etc.
I got access to these by using rosmsg list | grep std_msgs



 	-YES.. There can be multiple publishers within the same topic..
It can be pretty messy but it works. In this case subscriber of the
topic catches all of the messages they publish.


	-rospy.spin() holds the process until the ROS is closed or node is interrupted.
	rospy.is_shutdown() is used when the programm need to do something else besides just cathcing messages.
